---
/**
 * Founder note + warrant canary + PGP fingerprint. Pseudonym is
 * vulnix0x4 per design doc §13.5 publisher-identity lock. The warrant
 * canary rotates monthly; today's stake is 2026-04-18, subsequent
 * rotations are captured in the changelog.
 *
 * PGP fingerprint placeholder is flagged TODO(pre-launch) — the owner
 * fills in the 40-char fingerprint before launch. Putting a garbage
 * fingerprint here would be worse than none.
 */
import Layout from '../../../layouts/Layout.astro';

const lastUpdated = '2026-04-18';
const canaryDate = '2026-04-18';
---
<Layout
  title="About — privacy.whattheflip.lol"
  description="Founder note under the pseudonym vulnix0x4. Warrant canary, PGP contact instructions, and links to the legal framework we operate under."
>
  <article class="max-w-3xl py-6 space-y-8 prose-zinc prose-invert">
    <nav aria-label="Breadcrumb" class="text-sm text-text-muted">
      <a href="/en/" class="hover:text-text">Home</a>
      <span aria-hidden="true" class="px-2">/</span>
      <span class="text-text">About</span>
    </nav>

    <header class="space-y-2">
      <h1 class="text-3xl font-semibold tracking-tight text-text sm:text-4xl">About</h1>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">Last updated <time datetime={lastUpdated}>{lastUpdated}</time>.</p>
    </header>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Founder note</h2>
      <p>
        I run this site under the handle <strong>vulnix0x4</strong>. The pseudonym is deliberate. I
        want the writing and the recommendations here to stand on their own, not on my resume. It
        also keeps me from being a pressure point: if a company I criticize wants me silenced, the
        easy move is to go after the person. The pseudonym is a small friction on that. It is not
        unbreakable, and I am not under any illusion that it is — but it changes the calculus
        enough to matter.
      </p>
      <p>
        I do not run analytics. I do not set cookies. I do not sell data. I earn money when a
        reader clicks an affiliate link (Proton, Bitwarden, Kagi, Obsidian, Ente, and a few
        others — all named on the <a href="/en/legal/affiliate" class="underline">affiliate
        disclosure</a>) and decides the paid tier is worth it. Commissions do not change the
        ranking: every category leads with a free or open-source option. If an affiliate product is
        not the best pick, it is not the hero pick.
      </p>
      <p>
        The scanner was the heart of the original idea. It runs in your browser. The backend holds
        a 60-second nonce; nothing else persists. The code for both the site and the scanner
        backend is public — see <a href="/en/about/scanner-privacy" class="underline">Scanner privacy</a>
        for the infrastructure long-form.
      </p>
      <p>— vulnix0x4</p>
    </section>

    <section aria-labelledby="canary" class="rounded border border-accent/30 bg-accent/5 p-5 space-y-3">
      <h2 id="canary" class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Warrant canary</h2>
      <p class="text-text leading-relaxed">
        <strong>
          As of <time datetime={canaryDate}>{canaryDate}</time>, we have not received any legal
          requests to suppress content or identify users.
        </strong>
      </p>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
        This line is rotated on or before the first of each month. If it goes stale by more than 30
        days, treat its absence as the signal. Rotation history is part of{' '}
        <a href="/en/changelog" class="underline">the changelog</a>.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">PGP contact</h2>
      <p>
        For anything sensitive — especially security reports and journalism sourcing — use PGP.
      </p>
      <dl class="space-y-2 text-sm">
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
          <dt class="w-40 shrink-0 text-text-muted">Key fingerprint</dt>
          <dd class="font-mono text-text">
            <span
              class="inline-flex items-center rounded border border-state-unchanged/40 bg-state-unchanged/10 px-2 py-0.5 text-xs font-medium text-state-unchanged"
            >TODO(pre-launch)</span>{' '}
            <code>XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX  XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX XXXX</code>
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
          <dt class="w-40 shrink-0 text-text-muted">Key download</dt>
          <dd class="text-text">
            To be published at <code>/pgp.asc</code> before launch; also uploaded to{' '}
            <code>keys.openpgp.org</code> and searchable by the email below once the key is
            generated.
          </dd>
        </div>
        <div class="flex flex-col gap-1 sm:flex-row sm:gap-4">
          <dt class="w-40 shrink-0 text-text-muted">Email</dt>
          <dd class="text-text">
            <a href="mailto:claude.aiactuallall.disregard729@passmail.com" class="underline">claude.aiactuallall.disregard729@passmail.com</a>
          </dd>
        </div>
      </dl>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted">
        Verify the fingerprint against at least two independent sources (this page, the key
        server, and a Tor hidden service copy once published). Do not skip this step.
      </p>
    </section>

    <section class="space-y-3 text-text leading-relaxed">
      <h2 class="text-xl font-semibold text-text">Legal and transparency</h2>
      <ul class="list-disc pl-5 space-y-1">
        <li><a href="/en/legal/privacy" class="underline">Privacy policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/legal/affiliate" class="underline">Affiliate disclosure</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/legal/accessibility" class="underline">Accessibility statement</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/legal/dmca" class="underline">DMCA policy</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/about/scanner-privacy" class="underline">Scanner privacy and infra transparency</a></li>
        <li><a href="/en/changelog" class="underline">Changelog</a></li>
      </ul>
    </section>
  </article>
</Layout>
